headline: S&P 500 Nears Record as Markets Shrug Off Shutdown Fears
summary: The S&P 500 and tech-heavy Nasdaq looked set to cruise higher on Tuesday as Wall Street looked past the threat of another government shutdown, while the precious metals rally was running out of steam.  Futures tracking the S&P 500 climbed 0.3%, putting the market benchmark on course to pass 7,000 points for the first time ever.  Contracts tied to the Nasdaq 100 added 0.6%.

headline: Boeing's sales jump nearly 60% in 4Q, bolstered by strong rise in airplane deliveries
summary: Boeing's sales surged nearly 60% in the fourth quarter as the aerospace company digs itself out of a string of crises that tarnished its reputation.  Boeing had 160 commercial deliveries in the quarter, more than double the 57 deliveries in the prior-year period.  “We made significant progress on our recovery in 2025 and have set the foundation to keep our momentum going in the year ahead,” Boeing CEO Kelly Ortberg said in a statement on Tuesday.

headline: Boeing, Israel's Technion to develop sustainable aviation fuel, as sector grapples with 2050 goal
summary: JERUSALEM, Jan 27 (Reuters) - Boeing and Israel's Technion university said on Tuesday they were beginning to develop Sustainable Aviation Fuel (SAF) from ​feedstocks including green hydrogen and carbon dioxide to enable the aviation ‌sector's long-term growth. SAF, made largely from waste or used cooking oil, can cut emissions significantly compared with ‌traditional jet fuel.

headline: Boeing Earnings Trounced Expectations. Why the Stock Is Dropping.
summary: Boeing  stock was dropping even after the company reported far better-than-expected fourth-quarter earnings, aided by a gain on an asset sale.  Headline numbers look strong, but EPS included an $11.83 per share benefit from the sale of Boeing’s Digital Aviation Solutions business.  Boeing stock was down 2.3% in premarket trading at $242.76, while  futures were up 0.2% and  futures were down 0.6%.
